{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:36:48.209Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Placing long documents correctly"},{"type":"text","text":" in your prompt is the single most impactful technique for long-context prompting. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Put documents at the top and your question at the bottom"},{"type":"text","text":" — this can improve response quality by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"up to 30%"},{"type":"text","text":" for very large inputs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key insight:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"A large context window does not guarantee that the model pays equal attention to every part of a long document.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Core Principle: Document First, Question Last"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why This Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Attention follows a U-shape:"},{"type":"text","text":" Claude's attention is strongest at the beginning and end of the context window, weakest in the middle."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Anthropic's testing reveals:"},{"type":"text","text":" Placing lengthy documents (20K+ tokens) at the beginning of the prompt, before the actual query, significantly enhances response quality."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When your query comes after the context,"},{"type":"text","text":" the model has already \"read\" the full document before generating — significantly improving response quality."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic Pattern"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n{{LONG_DOCUMENT_TEXT}}\n</document>\n\nBased on the document above, what are the three main risks\nidentified in the financial analysis?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structure:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Top:"},{"type":"text","text":" Document content wrapped in XML tags\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bottom:"},{"type":"text","text":" Query or instructions"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Document Placement Strategies"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy 1: Single Document"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Place your long documents and inputs (20K+ tokens) near the top of your prompt, above your query, instructions, and examples.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n{{FULL_DOCUMENT_TEXT}}\n</document>\n\nInstructions:\n1. Summarize the key points\n2. Identify action items\n3. Extract important dates\n\nQuestion: What are the top 3 priorities mentioned?"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy 2: Multiple Documents with Indexing"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"When working with several documents, label them clearly so the model can reference and distinguish them.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<documents>\n<document index=\"1\">\n<source>Q3 Earnings Report</source>\n<content>{{EARNINGS_REPORT_TEXT}}</content>\n</document>\n\n<document index=\"2\">\n<source>Competitor Analysis</source>\n<content>{{COMPETITOR_ANALYSIS_TEXT}}</content>\n</document>\n</documents>\n\nCompare revenue growth between our Q3 results and the competitor analysis.\nCite which document supports each claim."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key features:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Indexed documents"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each has a number\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Source metadata"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document name\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Content separation"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<content>"},{"type":"text","text":" tags\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Citation requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model cites sources"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Model can cite sources"},{"type":"text","text":" — Verify claims\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distinguish content"},{"type":"text","text":" — Prevent confusion\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reference by index"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Document 1 mentions...\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy 3: Hierarchical Structure with Metadata"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Structure documents with XML tags. When using multiple documents, wrap each in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" tags with metadata subtags.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<documents>\n<document index=\"1\">\n<source>Contract Agreement</source>\n<type>Legal</type>\n<date>2024-01-15</date>\n<content>\n{{CONTRACT_TEXT}}\n</content>\n</document>\n\n<document index=\"2\">\n<source>Terms of Service</source>\n<type>Legal</type>\n<date>2024-03-01</date>\n<content>\n{{TERMS_TEXT}}\n</content>\n</document>\n</documents>\n\n找出所有 termination clauses across both documents.\nList each clause with its source document."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Metadata subtags:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<source>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document name\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<type>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Category (Legal, Technical, etc.)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<date>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Creation/review date"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy 4: Working Brief Before Full Document"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Working brief before full document provides decision context and constraints.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<working_brief>\nContext: Reviewing contracts for a potential merger\nGoal: Identify all termination clauses and their conditions\nConstraints:\n- Must extract exact clause text\n- Include section numbers\n- Note any unusual conditions\n</working_brief>\n\n<document>\n{{FULL_CONTRACT_TEXT}}\n</document>\n\nExtract all termination clauses with their exact text and section numbers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Working brief includes:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context"},{"type":"text","text":" — Why you're doing this\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Goal"},{"type":"text","text":" — What you want to achieve\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" — Limitations and requirements"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Provides decision context"},{"type":"text","text":" — Helps model understand purpose\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sets constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" — Limits scope\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Anchors attention"},{"type":"text","text":" — Focuses on what's important"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strategy 5: Curated Excerpts for Key Facts"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Curated excerpts for key facts anchors model attention to what matters.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<key_excerpts>\n<excerpt priority=\"high\">\nSource: Q3 Earnings Report, Page 12\n\"The company projected 15% revenue growth for Q4.\"\n</excerpt>\n\n<excerpt priority=\"high\">\nSource: Q3 Earnings Report, Page 15\n\"Operating expenses increased by 8% compared to Q3.\"\n</excerpt>\n\n<excerpt priority=\"medium\">\nSource: Competitor Analysis, Page 8\n\"Competitor X launched similar product in March 2024.\"\n</excerpt>\n</key_excerpts>\n\n<document>\n{{FULL_DOCUMENT_TEXT}}\n</document>\n\nBased on the key excerpts and full document above:\n1. What are the growth projections?\n2. How do expenses compare?\n3. What competitive threats exist?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Anchors attention"},{"type":"text","text":" — Highlights what matters\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduces noise"},{"type":"text","text":" — Focuses on key facts\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Priority-based"},{"type":"text","text":" — High/medium/low importance"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced Techniques"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 1: Sandwich / Bookend Pattern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Structure long prompts accordingly — critical instructions at the edges, reference material in the middle.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"[INSTRUCTIONS AT START]\n<document>\n{{LONG_DOCUMENT_CONTENT}}\n</document>\n[QUERY AT END]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Beginning"},{"type":"text","text":" — Strong attention, set context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Middle"},{"type":"text","text":" — Weakest attention, reference material\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"End"},{"type":"text","text":" — Strong attention, query"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 2: Ground Responses in Quotes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"For long document tasks, ask Claude to quote relevant parts first before carrying out its task.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n{{CONTRACT_TEXT}}\n</document>\n\nFirst, extract the exact quotes from the contract that relate to\ntermination clauses. Place them in <quotes> tags.\n\nThen, based only on those quotes, summarize the termination\nconditions in plain language."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounding reduces hallucination"},{"type":"text","text":" — Forces evidence first\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verification easy"},{"type":"text","text":" — See quotes + answer\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Signal of missing info"},{"type":"text","text":" — If no quote found, answer might not exist"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 3: Section Tags and Separators"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Tagging sections, using clear separators... are further best practices for maximizing output relevance and reliability.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n<section name=\"introduction\">\n{{INTRODUCTION_TEXT}}\n</section>\n\n<section name=\"main_body\">\n{{MAIN_BODY_TEXT}}\n</section>\n\n<section name=\"conclusion\">\n{{CONCLUSION_TEXT}}\n</section>\n</document>\n\n---\n\n<instructions>\n1. Summarize introduction\n2. Extract key points from main body\n3. Identify conclusion recommendations\n</instructions>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Increases retrieval"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear sections\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Answer clarity"},{"type":"text","text":" — Separated content\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reference by section"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"In the conclusion...\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 4: Chunking & Progressive Disclosure"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Techniques for chunking, progressive disclosure, and maintaining coherence across entire codebases and book-length documents.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chunking approach:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chunk 1:\n<document index=\"1\" part=\"1\">\n{{FIRST_20K_TOKENS}}\n</document>\n\nChunk 2:\n<document index=\"1\" part=\"2\">\n{{SECOND_20K_TOKENS}}\n</document>\n\nChunk 3:\n<document index=\"1\" part=\"3\">\n{{THIRD_20K_TOKENS}}\n</document>\n\nSummarize all three chunks together."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Progressive disclosure:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start"},{"type":"text","text":" — High-level summary\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Then"},{"type":"text","text":" — Specific details\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Finally"},{"type":"text","text":" — Deep analysis"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 5: Chunk-and-Combine for Summarization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Piecewise document summarization: For summarizing long documents, break them into sections and summarize each one separately. Then, combine.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Process:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Step 1: Chunk document\nchunks = split_document(doc, chunk_size=20000)\n\n# Step 2: Summarize each chunk\nfor i, chunk in enumerate(chunks):\n    summary_i = summarize(chunk)\n\n# Step 3: Combine summaries\nfinal_summary = combine_all(summaries)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle beyond 200K"},{"type":"text","text":" — When document exceeds limit\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Quality preservation"},{"type":"text","text":" — Not losing context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallel processing"},{"type":"text","text":" — Can process chunks separately"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Document Formatting Guidelines"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Format 1: Clear Separators"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Document formatting guidelines that improve retrieval accuracy.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML tags"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<section>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<content>"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Horizontal rules"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"---"},{"type":"text","text":" between sections\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Headers"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"#"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"##"},{"type":"text","text":" for structure\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Whitespace"},{"type":"text","text":" — Empty lines between blocks"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Format 2: Numbered Items"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"One 'trick' you can use if you just want to tabulate an extremely long list of stuff, is to use a sequence bootstrapping / FSM method.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Item 1: {{CONTENT_1}}\nItem 2: {{CONTENT_2}}\nItem 3: {{CONTENT_3}}\n...\nItem 992: {{CONTENT_992}}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequential counter"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model can track\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tabulate easily"},{"type":"text","text":" — Create structured output\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stop sequence"},{"type":"text","text":" — Can terminate at specific item"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Format 3: Metadata Headers"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Claude's long-context performance depends not only on raw capacity but also on prompt structure and operational constraints.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Document: Contract Agreement\n# Type: Legal\n# Date: 2024-01-15\n# Parties: Company A, Company B\n# Status: Active\n\n{{FULL_CONTRACT_TEXT}}"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When Full Context Isn't Enough"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Approach 1: Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"When you hit these limits, you need a different approach — fetching only the relevant pieces at query time.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decision framework:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Full 200K context"},{"type":"text","text":" — When document is critical and < 200K tokens\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RAG"},{"type":"text","text":" — When document is huge or you need specific sections\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summarization chains"},{"type":"text","text":" — When overview is sufficient"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Approach 2: Cost-Benefit Analysis"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"When to use the full 200K vs. RAG vs. summarization chains. Cost comparisons between approaches, latency tradeoffs, and decision frameworks for different document sizes and task types.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Considerations:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost"},{"type":"text","text":" — Full context vs. RAG\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Latency"},{"type":"text","text":" — Processing time tradeoffs\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document size"},{"type":"text","text":" — Break-even points\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task type"},{"type":"text","text":" — Quality requirements"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices Summary"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Documents First, Question Last"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The single most impactful technique for long-context prompts: place your documents at the top and your question at the bottom.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Impact:"},{"type":"text","text":" Up to 30% quality improvement"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Use XML Tags"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Structure documents with XML tags. When using multiple documents, wrap each in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" tags with metadata subtags.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tags:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Main wrapper\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<source>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document name\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<content>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Actual text\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<section>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document sections"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Include Index and Metadata"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Indexed documents let the model cite sources — and let you verify its claims.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Index number\n- Source name\n- Type/category\n- Date"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Ground in Quotes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Grounding dramatically reduces hallucination. If the model can't find a relevant quote, that's a useful signal — the answer might not be in the document.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pattern:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Extract exact quotes\n2. Place in <quotes> tags\n3. Answer based only on quotes"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Add Working Brief"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Working brief before full document provides decision context and constraints.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Context\n- Goal\n- Constraints"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Use Clear Separators"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Section tags and separators increase retrieval and answer clarity.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- XML tags\n- Horizontal rules (---)\n- Headers (#, ##)\n- Whitespace"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7. Chunk Large Documents"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Techniques for chunking, progressive disclosure, and maintaining coherence across entire codebases and book-length documents.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When:"},{"type":"text","text":" Document exceeds 200K tokens or too large for single request"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Process:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. Split into chunks\n2. Process each separately\n3. Combine results"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Placing long documents correctly"},{"type":"text","text":" is the most impactful long-context technique:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core principle:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document First, Question Last"},{"type":"text","text":" — Place documents at top, question at bottom\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Impact:"},{"type":"text","text":" Up to 30% quality improvement"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Attention follows U-shape"},{"type":"text","text":" — Strongest at beginning/end, weakest in middle\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Model reads full document"},{"type":"text","text":" — Before generating query response"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5 placement strategies:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Single document"},{"type":"text","text":" — Simple "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","text":" wrapper\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multiple with indexing"},{"type":"text","text":" — Indexed "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<documents>"},{"type":"text","text":" with source metadata\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hierarchical with metadata"},{"type":"text","text":" — Type, date, source tags\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Working brief first"},{"type":"text","text":" — Context before document\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Curated excerpts"},{"type":"text","text":" — Key facts with priority"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5 advanced techniques:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sandwich pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" — Instructions at edges, content in middle\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ground in quotes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Extract quotes before answering\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Section tags"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear separators between sections\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chunking"},{"type":"text","text":" — Split into parts, combine results\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Numbered items"},{"type":"text","text":" — Sequential counter for tabulation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document formatting:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear separators"},{"type":"text","text":" — XML, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"---"},{"type":"text","text":", headers, whitespace\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Numbered items"},{"type":"text","text":" — Item 1, Item 2, Item 3\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Metadata headers"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document, type, date, parties"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When full context fails:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"RAG"},{"type":"text","text":" — Fetch relevant pieces at query time\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost-benefit analysis"},{"type":"text","text":" — Compare full context vs. RAG vs. summarization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7 best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Documents first"},{"type":"text","text":" — Top of prompt\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use XML tags"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<source>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<content>"},{"type":"text","text":"\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Include index"},{"type":"text","text":" — Cite sources, verify claims\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ground in quotes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Reduce hallucination\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Add working brief"},{"type":"text","text":" — Context and constraints\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use separators"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear structure\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chunk large docs"},{"type":"text","text":" — Split when too big"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompt ordering and structure are critical for reliable large document processing\""},{"type":"text","text":" — documents first, query last."}]}]}}
